Bash

# Check the main Agent/Manager directory
ls -ld /var/ossec/

# Check the Indexer configuration directory
ls -ld /etc/wazuh-indexer/

# Check the Dashboard application directory
ls -ld /usr/share/wazuh-dashboard/
2. Check Critical Binaries (Executables)
These are the command-line tools needed to manage and troubleshoot Wazuh.

Bash

# The log test tool we couldn't find before
ls -l /var/ossec/bin/ossec-logtest

# The main Wazuh control script
ls -l /var/ossec/bin/wazuh-control

# The agent control script
ls -l /var/ossec/bin/agent_control
3. Check Service and Configuration Files
These files are essential for the services to run.

Bash

# Check the Wazuh agent/manager configuration file
ls -l /var/ossec/etc/ossec.conf

# Check the Wazuh Indexer configuration file
ls -l /etc/wazuh-indexer/opensearch.yml
